elements.title: a mirror on the Moon
elements.contents: ... that scientists shooting lasers at a mirror on the Moon (pictured) discovered that their telescope was not where it should be?

elements.title: trial of Lina E.

elements.title: Poppy Garden
elements.contents: ... that none of the actors in Poppy Garden, a film depicting a father and son's struggle for survival during the Colombian conflict, had previously acted in a film?

elements.title: Just Another Day

elements.title: Smoke over Birkenau
elements.contents: ... that Smoke over Birkenau by Polish writer Seweryna Szmaglewska, published in 1945, was one of the first and most influential works about the Auschwitz–Birkenau concentration camp?

elements.title: a mural of Alexia as a superhero
elements.contents: ... that when TVBoy's daughter said she wanted to be a footballer like Alexia Putellas, he painted a mural of Alexia as a superhero to inspire other girls?

elements.title: The Owl and the Pussy Cat
elements.contents: ... that Igor Stravinsky suggested that performances of his song "The Owl and the Pussy Cat" should be "a little hooted, a little meowed, a little grunted"?
